# 🧠 OS Concept 1: Event-Driven Architecture

## 1️⃣ Simple Idea

Instead of constantly checking for work:

👉 system reacts when events happen.

---

## 🧠 Real-World Analogy

Doorbell 🔔

You don’t keep opening door repeatedly.

You react only when bell rings.

---

## ⚙️ Example Events

* user clicks button
* payment received
* SOS triggered
* message arrives

---

## ⚙️ Flow

```text id="5k9x1a"
Event occurs
   ↓
Event handler runs
```

---

## Why Powerful?

✔ scalable
✔ responsive
✔ efficient resource usage

---

## 🔗 Connection

Interrupts in OS are event-driven ideas.

---

## 🎯 Placement Question

**Q: Why event-driven systems scale well?**

👉 Because resources are used only when events occur.

---

## 🧠 Memory Trick

```text id="v7m2pk"
Event happens → system reacts
```

